00:54:30,930 --> 00:54:33,170
{\an8}Dad, I'm not.</font>

633
00:54:33,470 --> 00:54:34,600
{\an8}I'm fine.</font>

634
00:54:35,040 --> 00:54:36,770
{\an8}You're not.</font>

635
00:54:37,240 --> 00:54:39,640
{\an8}You are not fine. Jake.</font>

636
00:54:40,240 --> 00:54:43,410
{\an8}Coming here was a terrible...
terrible idea.</font>

637
00:54:43,750 --> 00:54:45,330
{\an8}I'm sorry, I lied ..</font>

638
00:54:46,230 --> 00:54:48,500
{\an8}Set your alarm for 8:00 am.</font>

639
00:54:49,100 --> 00:54:50,760
{\an8}I want to get to the beach early.</font>

640
00:54:51,100 --> 00:54:55,170
{\an8}The rest of the time left on this
crap-O-island, we're sticking together.</font>

641
00:54:55,940 --> 00:54:57,310
{\an8}Where are you going?</font>

642
00:54:57,650 --> 00:54:59,720
{\an8}Downstairs for a drink.</font>

643
00:55:48,070 --> 00:55:51,210
{\an8}<i>Dearest Peregrine:
I don't wish to alarm you...</i></font>

644
00:55:51,610 --> 00:55:54,510
{\an8}<i>but one of my informants
sent me this.</i></font>

645
00:55:55,050 --> 00:55:59,730
{\an8}<i>It would appear that some of Mr. Barron's
group were in Black Pool, England.</i></font>

646
00:56:00,530 --> 00:56:04,730
{\an8}<i>"If I recall,
Ms. Avocet has a loop there."</i></font>

647
00:56:05,270 --> 00:56:09,140
{\an8}<i>"Please warn her and suggest that
she make a new one right away."</i></font>

648
00:56:09,500 --> 00:56:10,710
{\an8}<i>"Well hidden."</i></font>

649
00:56:11,020 --> 00:56:18,120
{\an8}<i>And take the greatest care yourself.
With Love, Abe. January 2016.</i></font>

650
00:56:35,790 --> 00:56:38,860
{\an8}Who is ready to hit the beach?</font>

651
00:56:44,000 --> 00:56:46,170
{\an8}Oh my goodness.</font>

652
00:56:46,700 --> 00:56:48,250
{\an8}Unbelievable!</font>

653
00:56:48,980 --> 00:56:51,080
{\an8}I'm right in the middle
of a nesting are?</font>

654
00:56:51,520 --> 00:56:53,650
{\an8}What kind of idiot does that?</font>

655
00:56:54,790 --> 00:56:58,120
{\an8}Actually, the main nesting
area is over there.</font>

656
00:56:58,590 --> 00:57:00,000
{\an8}I can show you, if you like.</font>

657
00:57:00,340 --> 00:57:02,580
{\an8}It's marvelous to meet
a fellow bird-spotter!</font>

658
00:57:02,810 --> 00:57:04,370
{\an8}John Lamont. Franklyn Portman.</font>

659
00:57:04,740 --> 00:57:06,040
{\an8}This is my son, Jake.</font>

660
00:57:06,380 --> 00:57:07,910
{\an8}John Newmont.</font>

661
00:57:08,250 --> 00:57:10,080
{\an8}That's a hell of a camera you got there.</font>

662
00:57:10,510 --> 00:57:12,760
{\an8}Oh, thank you,
is absolutely fantastic.</font>

663
00:57:13,230 --> 00:57:15,670
{\an8}I am here to do some snaps
for a book I'm writing.</font>

664
00:57:16,000 --> 00:57:19,600
{\an8}So, you gentlemen are
here on holiday?</font>

665
00:57:29,550 --> 00:57:31,820
{\an8}So, you are not coming
to the beach today?</font>

666
00:57:32,160 --> 00:57:33,420
{\an8}What's the point?</font>

667
00:57:33,790 --> 00:57:36,970
{\an8}That guys gonna cover ******
on some big glossy book,</font>

668
00:57:36,980 --> 00:57:38,920
{\an8}no ones even wanna look at mine.</font>

669
00:57:39,940 --> 00:57:42,710
{\an8}I might just have
a nice afternoon nap.</font>

670
00:57:43,340 --> 00:57:46,160
{\an8}I don't suppose you saw uncle Oggie
on you travels this morning, did you?</font>

671
00:57:46,210 --> 00:57:48,190
{\an8}He's usually here by now.</font>

672
00:57:48,530 --> 00:57:49,830
{\an8}I could go look for him.</font>

673
00:57:50,130 --> 00:57:52,260
{\an8}You're not going anywhere</font>

674
00:58:27,190 --> 00:58:30,660
{\an8}Jake, you're back! Come and play!</font>

675
00:58:34,000 --> 00:58:36,170
{\an8}I need to see
to Ms. Peregrine first.</font>

676
00:58:36,540 --> 00:58:38,420
{\an8}Do you know where she is?</font>

677
00:58:42,820 --> 00:58:45,620
{\an8}Jake, you're back.
How wonderful!</font>

678
00:58:46,160 --> 00:58:47,720
{\an8}How's it doing?</font>

679
00:58:48,230 --> 00:58:50,000
{\an8}Emma said it was an Ymbryne.</font>

680
00:58:50,370 --> 00:58:53,510
{\an8}She, not 'it'. Ymbrynes
are always female.</font>

681
00:58:53,870 --> 00:58:56,580
{\an8}And Emma was quite correct.
This is Ms. Avocet.</font>

682
00:58:57,010 --> 00:59:00,110
{\an8}Her loop is in Black Pool England.</font>

683
00:59:02,230 --> 00:59:04,660
{\an8}That was a private letter, Jake.</font>

684
00:59:07,200 --> 00:59:09,830
{\an8}Who is Mr Barron?</font>

685
00:59:11,000 --> 00:59:14,910
{\an8}Ms. Peregrine, if my grandpa was
involved with dangerous people</font>

686
00:59:15,320 --> 00:59:17,620
{\an8}I need to tell the police.</font>

687
00:59:17,990 --> 00:59:19,750
{\an8}To the police?</font>

688
00:59:20,250 --> 00:59:23,090
{\an8}Are you implying Abe
died an unnatural death?</font>

689
00:59:23,460 --> 00:59:26,400
{\an8}I found him in the woods
with eyes missing.</font>

690
00:59:27,070 --> 00:59:30,340
{\an8}I'd say that was pretty unnatural.</font>

691
00:59:33,740 --> 00:59:36,910
{\an8}Unless essential. I don't
discuss unpleasant matters.</font>

692
00:59:37,380 --> 00:59:40,160
{\an8}An Ymbryne's is a duty to
protect children, Jake.</font>

693
00:59:40,760 --> 00:59:42,830
{\an8}I am not a child.</font>

694
00:59:43,500 --> 00:59:46,200
{\an8}He wanted you to tell me everything.</font>

695
00:59:50,470 --> 00:59:53,120
{\an8}Oh. How frustrating for you.</font>

696
00:59:53,680 --> 00:59:57,120
{\an8}Between Ms. Peregrine rules and
my ******* not to scare you off.</font>

697
00:59:57,620 --> 00:59:59,720
{\an8}It's like no ones
telling you anything?!</font>

698
01:00:00,290 --> 01:00:02,460
{\an8}So why don't you then?</font>

699
01:00:02,790 --> 01:00:04,640
{\an8}It's not like you want me here.</font>

700
01:00:04,940 --> 01:00:06,070
{\an8}Enoch, you can't.</font>

701
01:00:06,340 --> 01:00:07,910
{\an8}You promised.</font>

702
01:00:08,240 --> 01:00:09,680
{\an8}Olive is right.</font>

703
01:00:10,080 --> 01:00:13,050
{\an8}However, I know someone
who can break the rules.</font>

704
01:00:13,450 --> 01:00:15,760
{\an8}Want to meet him?</font>

705
01:00:15,790 --> 01:00:18,560
{\an8}Enoch, do not do this! Please.</font>

706
01:00:19,100 --> 01:00:22,530
{\an8}You didn't want us to spend time together.
That's what you said.</font>

707
01:00:24,540 --> 01:00:26,840
{\an8}Well, here we all are.</font>

708
01:00:27,300 --> 01:00:29,120
{\an8}Move, Olive.</font>

709
01:00:29,520 --> 01:00:33,190
{\an8}If you're going to be like then
I do not want to be your friend.</font>

710
01:00:35,520 --> 01:00:39,560
{\an8}Enoch! Leave Victor alone.
It really upsets Bromwyn.</font>

711
01:00:40,070 --> 01:00:43,170
{\an8}Stop fussing, Fiona. Don't you
think Jake should meet everybody?</font>

712
01:00:43,470 --> 01:00:45,090
{\an8}He's trying to frighten
you away, Jake.</font>

713
01:00:45,110 --> 01:00:47,510
{\an8}He was always jealous of Abe
and now he's jealous of you.</font>

714
01:00:47,680 --> 01:00:50,450
{\an8}Come and play with us instead</font>

715
01:00:53,860 --> 01:00:56,900
{\an8}I'd quite like to meet Victor.</font>

716
01:01:02,600 --> 01:01:04,540
{\an8}After You.</font>

717
01:01:12,660 --> 01:01:14,320
{\an8}Hello Victor.</font>

718
01:01:14,790 --> 01:01:18,740
{\an8}I'm Jake. I'm sorry to disturb...</font>

719
01:01:21,780 --> 01:01:23,280
{\an8}He can't hear you.</font>

720
01:01:48,460 --> 01:01:53,030
{\an8}Hello Jake, I'm Victor. Do you
want to know what killed me?</font>

721
01:01:59,910 --> 01:02:01,860
{\an8}Ah, there you are.
Is he not with you?</font>

722
01:02:01,870 --> 01:02:03,660
{\an8}Its time for our daily walk.</font>

723
01:02:06,560 --> 01:02:10,930
{\an8}Emma, Who killed Victor? Was it
the people with the white eyes?</font>

724
01:02:10,930 --> 01:02:15,030
{\an8}I asked you not to ask questions.
I saw one the night my grandpa died.</font>

725
01:02:18,820 --> 01:02:21,340
{\an8}If it really was one, you
have to tell Ms. Peregrinee.</font>

726
01:02:21,350 --> 01:02:23,950
{\an8}Could you recognize you recognize
him from a photograph?</font>

727
01:02:23,950 --> 01:02:25,150
{\an8}Do you have one?</font>

728
01:02:25,160 --> 01:02:28,550
{\an8}Then come on.
There's somewhere I go to be alone.</font>

729
01:02:28,560 --> 01:02:29,980
{\an8}I have things there.</font>

730
01:03:07,540 --> 01:03:10,970
{\an8}- Is this the place?
- No. This is how we get there.</font>

731
01:03:30,670 --> 01:03:34,250
{\an8}Emma! Your shoes! Lead shoes!</font>

732
01:05:36,140 --> 01:05:41,240
{\an8}- Welcome to my secret hideout.
- How? How did you...</font>

733
01:05:41,910 --> 01:05:47,630
{\an8}Air. My peculiarity.
It does what I want</font>

734
01:06:06,960 --> 01:06:12,210
{\an8}Jake. Before your grandfather retired,
he asked me to keep this safe.</font>

735
01:06:29,870 --> 01:06:33,800
{\an8}This is my grandpa's old map.
It shows you where the loops are.</font>

736
01:06:44,220 --> 01:06:48,360
{\an8}That's him, thats the man I saw.
Who is he?</font>

737
01:06:48,370 --> 01:06:51,380
{\an8}Thats Barron. He is the Leader.</font>

738
01:06:52,740 --> 01:06:56,830
{\an8}Leader of what?
Who are these people?</font>

739
01:06:56,840 --> 01:06:59,960
{\an8}Bad people... bad peculiars.</font>

740
01:07:01,200 --> 01:07:03,880
{\an8}Abe dedicated his life
to hunting them down.</font>

741
01:07:03,890 --> 01:07:05,980
{\an8}These are the ones
he never found.</font>

742
01:07:06,730 --> 01:07:09,340
{\an8}What do you mean "hunting"?</font>

743
01:07:11,610 --> 01:07:17,060
{\an8}They raided homes. Whole homes
full of children left for dead.</font>

744
01:07:17,070 --> 01:07:18,620
{\an8}Abe took lives...</font>

745
01:07:18,620 --> 01:07:19,670
{\an8}To save life's.</font>

746
01:07:19,680 --> 01:07:22,970
{\an8}He only retired when you
were born to protect you.</font>

747
01:07:23,460 --> 01:07:25,060
{\an8}From what?</font>

748
01:07:26,670 --> 01:07:31,670
{\an8}If I tell you the rest, you have
to promise not to run away.</font>

749
01:07:33,450 --> 01:07:35,570
{\an8}Jake, you belong here.</font>

750
01:07:35,580 --> 01:07:40,080
{\an8}You know that I don't.
I'm not like you.</font>

751
01:07:40,090 --> 01:07:42,160
{\an8}I'm just ordinary.</font>

752
01:07:42,170 --> 01:07:43,650
{\an8}No, but you're not.</font>

753
01:07:43,660 --> 01:07:47,710
{\an8}Jake, only a peculiar can
enter a time loop.</font>

754
01:07:50,450 --> 01:07:52,580
{\an8}No, that can't be right.</font>

755
01:07:52,590 --> 01:07:54,670
{\an8}I mean... I would know.</font>

756
01:07:54,680 --> 01:07:55,730
{\an8}Fine.</font>

757
01:07:56,650 --> 01:07:59,680
{\an8}Then I'll show you
something else.</font>

758
01:08:07,480 --> 01:08:08,810
{\an8}Hurry! You'll miss it.</font>

759
01:08:22,400 --> 01:08:25,100
{\an8}Ymbrynes usually pick the
perfect date to create a loop.</font>

760
01:08:25,110 --> 01:08:28,330
{\an8}But Ms. Peregrinee ..
had to make this one in a rush.</font>

761
01:08:29,440 --> 01:08:30,490
{\an8}Why?</font>

762
01:08:30,490 --> 01:08:33,940
{\an8}Because the Germans were about
to drop a bomb on the house.</font>

763
01:08:33,950 --> 01:08:36,290
{\an8}The point is, September
the 3rd, 1943...</font>

764
01:08:36,290 --> 01:08:37,780
{\an8}wasn't perfect.</font>

765
01:08:37,790 --> 01:08:41,750
{\an8}The thing that killed
Victor came back.</font>

766
01:09:08,490 --> 01:09:11,390
{\an8}- Wait, watch out!
- Shhh, all bets are off.</font>

767
01:09:39,740 --> 01:09:41,780
{\an8}You can see it, can't you?</font>

768
01:09:41,790 --> 01:09:43,070
{\an8}No one else can.</font>

769
01:09:43,080 --> 01:09:47,760
{\an8}Its invisible, Jake. That was
Abe's greatest gift of all.</font>

770
01:09:51,090 --> 01:09:53,510
{\an8}He could see the monsters.</font>

771
01:09:57,910 --> 01:10:02,420
{\an8}We call them 'Hollowgasts'.
Hollows. For short.</font>

772
01:10:02,420 --> 01:10:06,630
{\an8}My grandpa told me about people,
who turn into monsters.</font>

773
01:10:06,640 --> 01:10:08,330
{\an8}Is that what they are?</font>

774
01:10:08,330 --> 01:10:10,070
{\an8}I will explain everything, Jake.</font>

775
01:10:10,080 --> 01:10:12,130
{\an8}I fear its my duty
now considering...</font>

776
01:10:12,150 --> 01:10:14,300
{\an8}but you should know
that in doing so...</font>

777
01:10:14,300 --> 01:10:16,440
{\an8}I'm breaking a solemn promise.</font>

778
01:10:16,450 --> 01:10:19,620
{\an8}I knew you were peculiar
when you were born</font>

779
01:10:19,630 --> 01:10:21,350
{\an8}but your grandfather...</font>

780
01:10:21,360 --> 01:10:23,090
{\an8}forbid me to tell you anything.</font>

781
01:10:23,100 --> 01:10:26,490
{\an8}His dearest wish was for you
to have an ordinary childhood.</font>

782
01:10:26,490 --> 01:10:28,320
{\an8}Well I definitely had that.</font>

783
01:10:28,330 --> 01:10:32,040
{\an8}He intended to tell you the
truth when you turned 18.</font>

784
01:10:32,040 --> 01:10:37,430
{\an8}He hoped his bed-time
stories would pave the way.</font>

785
01:10:37,440 --> 01:10:39,160
{\an8}Here's my book.</font>

786
01:10:51,270 --> 01:10:52,940
{\an8}Many years ago,</font>

787
01:10:52,950 --> 01:10:56,550
{\an8}a splinter faction emerged
among our people.</font>

788
01:10:56,560 --> 01:10:59,450
{\an8}Disaffected peculiars
tired of living in loops.</font>

789
01:10:59,460 --> 01:11:01,800
{\an8}That's Mr. Barron.</font>

790
01:11:02,090 --> 01:11:06,030
{\an8}He believed that by harnessing the
essence of an Ymbryne's powers,</font>

791
01:11:06,040 --> 01:11:07,200
{\an8}he and his cronies.</font>

792
01:11:07,210 --> 01:11:11,970
{\an8}Could gain immortality and be
able to live outside loops.</font>

793
01:11:11,980 --> 01:11:14,120
{\an8}He devised an experiment.</font>

794
01:11:16,780 --> 01:11:18,180
{\an8}He kidnapped an Ymbryne</font>

795
01:11:18,190 --> 01:11:22,140
{\an8}not knowing or caring whether she
would survive the experiment.</font>

796
01:11:43,010 --> 01:11:47,640
{\an8}But the fate of Barron and his
group was more horrifying still.</font>

797
01:12:24,110 --> 01:12:26,710
{\an8}Why didn't Barron turn into one?</font>

798
01:12:39,540 --> 01:12:46,650
{\an8}He did. But years later he found a way to
reverse the effects... to regain humanity.</font>

799
01:12:46,990 --> 01:12:50,980
{\an8}They had become not immortal
gods... but Hollows.</font>

800
01:12:50,990 --> 01:12:54,990
{\an8}Invisible beasts, dangerous,
cold-blooded, deadly!</font>

801
01:12:55,300 --> 01:12:59,640
{\an8}Remember I told you they raided loops?
This is why.</font>

802
01:12:59,980 --> 01:13:03,910
{\an8}Barron discovered that by consuming
the eyes of other peculiars...</font>

803
01:13:03,920 --> 01:13:05,530
{\an8}especially children,</font>

804
01:13:13,770 --> 01:13:15,700
{\an8}He began to change.</font>

805
01:13:33,570 --> 01:13:36,940
{\an8}Consume enough, and a hollow can
fully regain its human form.</font>

806
01:13:39,050 --> 01:13:41,510
{\an8}Just as Barron and some
of his friends did.</font>

807
01:13:50,670 --> 01:13:54,050
{\an8}The rest of them are
stuck as Hollows.</font>

808
01:13:54,060 --> 01:13:57,940
{\an8}Are you saying that
Barron ate my uncle's...</font>

809
01:13:57,940 --> 01:14:00,180
{\an8}He needs no more eyes himself,</font>

810
01:14:00,190 --> 01:14:04,070
{\an8}but I fear he led a Hollow
to your grandfather, yes.</font>

811
01:14:05,860 --> 01:14:07,900
{\an8}After the first
attacks on Loops,</font>

812
01:14:07,910 --> 01:14:11,670
{\an8}we all got better at hiding
...making new loops... keeping our.</font>

813
01:14:11,680 --> 01:14:12,820
{\an8}Whereabouts secret.</font>

814
01:14:12,830 --> 01:14:15,920
{\an8}The Hollows grew more
desperate every year</font>

815
01:14:15,930 --> 01:14:18,780
{\an8}and Barron wishes to
help his friends.</font>

816
01:14:18,780 --> 01:14:22,920
{\an8}Miss Peregrine! Come quickly!
Miss Avocet's awake.</font>

817
01:14:29,740 --> 01:14:32,100
{\an8}Oh Miss Peregrine! They
found my new loop.</font>

818
01:14:32,110 --> 01:14:35,980
{\an8}The children... I tried to save them
but there were so many Hollows...</font>

819
01:14:35,990 --> 01:14:42,790
{\an8}- I don't know how I escaped.
- You are safe now.</font>

820
01:14:42,960 --> 01:14:44,280
{\an8}None of us are safe.</font>

821
01:14:44,300 --> 01:14:46,670
{\an8}They set up the
machine in my loop.</font>

822
01:14:46,830 --> 01:14:49,130
{\an8}They put in in the cellar
at Blackboat tower.</font>

823
01:14:49,140 --> 01:14:51,140
{\an8}- They're still there...
- The machine?</font>

824
01:14:51,140 --> 01:14:54,370
{\an8}The experiment.
They intend to do it again!</font>

825
01:14:54,390 --> 01:14:57,020
{\an8}This time, he's using
more Ymbrynes.</font>

826
01:14:57,020 --> 01:14:59,390
{\an8}He still wants to be immortal.</font>

827
01:15:02,670 --> 01:15:05,030
{\an8}Do Hollows only
attack peculiars?</font>

828
01:15:05,040 --> 01:15:07,760
{\an8}Of course not! They're
monsters, Jake,</font>

829
01:15:07,770 --> 01:15:10,690
{\an8}they'll slaughter
anything in their path.</font>

830
01:15:11,070 --> 01:15:13,610
{\an8}Well, some sheep on the
island were killed,</font>

831
01:15:13,620 --> 01:15:16,270
{\an8}You don't think they're
here already, do you?</font>

832
01:15:16,590 --> 01:15:20,390
{\an8}Have you seen anyone
with white eyes?</font>

833
01:15:22,300 --> 01:15:25,100
{\an8}I'm sorry children,
we can't remain here.</font>

834
01:15:25,240 --> 01:15:26,240
{\an8}What?</font>

835
01:15:26,250 --> 01:15:28,740
{\an8}We leave on the first ferry,
off the island tomorrow.</font>

836
01:15:28,750 --> 01:15:30,150
{\an8}Pack anything of importance.</font>

837
01:15:30,160 --> 01:15:32,310
{\an8}I'll make sandwiches
and lead you to bed.</font>

838
01:15:32,320 --> 01:15:35,020
{\an8}Are we leaving for good?
When are we coming back?</font>

839
01:15:35,020 --> 01:15:37,860
{\an8}Never. If Ms. Peregrine's not here
to reset the loop tomorrow night...</font>

840
01:15:37,860 --> 01:15:40,770
{\an8}- the house gets bombed.
- What? Our house?</font>

841
01:15:40,770 --> 01:15:43,890
{\an8}Don't cry, Miss Peregrine will find you
another lovely house... somewhere else.</font>

842
01:15:51,790 --> 01:15:55,820
{\an8}Once this loop closes, that's it!
I can't get back to my own time.</font>

843
01:15:55,830 --> 01:15:58,430
{\an8}You didn't seem
very happy there.</font>

844
01:15:58,440 --> 01:16:01,260
{\an8}I can't just leave!
I have a family.</font>

845
01:16:01,270 --> 01:16:05,310
{\an8}And you felt ordinary. Like
nothing you do changes anything.</font>

846
01:16:05,310 --> 01:16:09,270
{\an8}And, now you have a chance to do
something that changes everything.</font>

847
01:16:09,280 --> 01:16:11,280
{\an8}Jake, were in danger...</font>

848
01:16:11,280 --> 01:16:14,720
{\an8}and you're the only one
who can see the Hollows.</font>

849
01:16:14,730 --> 01:16:18,030
{\an8}Yeah, I see them sure
but, I'm not my grandpa.</font>

850
01:16:18,040 --> 01:16:19,300
{\an8}I'm not and I...I</font>

851
01:16:20,040 --> 01:16:22,440
{\an8}can't fight, I can't kill somebody...</font>

852
01:16:25,990 --> 01:16:30,180
{\an8}There's only one reason
that I'd stay here.</font>

853
01:16:30,190 --> 01:16:32,000
{\an8}Please!... just go.</font>

854
01:17:00,910 --> 01:17:04,030
{\an8}Jake... Jake, here you are!
Thank God!</font>

855
01:17:04,040 --> 01:17:07,400
{\an8}When I heard they found
a body, I freaked.</font>

856
01:17:31,770 --> 01:17:35,900
{\an8}- Are there stray dogs around here?
- What are you talking about?</font>

857
01:17:35,910 --> 01:17:37,240
{\an8}Its like,</font>

858
01:17:37,250 --> 01:17:42,550
{\an8}when they find an injured animal,
they go for the soft parts first.</font>

859
01:17:42,560 --> 01:17:45,530
{\an8}Same thing happened
to my father.</font>

860
01:17:45,540 --> 01:17:48,070
{\an8}The police are on their way.</font>

861
01:17:49,530 --> 01:17:50,730
{\an8}Dad, I gotta go?</font>

862
01:17:50,740 --> 01:17:52,310
{\an8}No... you don't Jake.</font>

863
01:17:52,330 --> 01:17:54,710
{\an8}If this wasn't an accident...</font>

864
01:17:54,710 --> 01:17:56,770
{\an8}there's a lunatic on the island.</font>

865
01:17:56,780 --> 01:18:01,480
{\an8}I've known everyone on this island,
my whole life except you and him...</font>

866
01:18:01,480 --> 01:18:03,590
{\an8}And he's been in the
pub all afternoon.</font>

867
01:18:03,610 --> 01:18:05,130
{\an8}So have I... I was sleeping.</font>

868
01:18:05,130 --> 01:18:07,390
{\an8}What about the blind fellow?
I mean...</font>

869
01:18:07,400 --> 01:18:10,780
{\an8}I assumed he was blind.
The gentleman with the dark glasses.</font>

870
01:18:10,790 --> 01:18:12,600
{\an8}Arrived on the same ferry as me.</font>

871
01:18:12,610 --> 01:18:20,020
{\an8}- I kept seeing him around.
- Jake! Jake!</font>

872
01:18:27,060 --> 01:18:33,110
{\an8}- Is your son alright?
- No, he has mental health issues.</font>

873
01:18:33,650 --> 01:18:37,050
{\an8}- I can't...
- Let me, I run 5 K's all the time.</font>

874
01:18:50,570 --> 01:18:51,840
{\an8}Hello!</font>

875
01:18:56,320 --> 01:18:59,850
{\an8}Hello! Is that you, young man?</font>

876
01:18:59,860 --> 01:19:04,330
{\an8}You came through?...
You're a peculiar?</font>

877
01:19:06,180 --> 01:19:09,960
{\an8}Oh yes, and I'm extremely
grateful to you.</font>

878
01:19:09,970 --> 01:19:14,190
{\an8}It's terribly hard... to
find loops these days.</font>

879
01:19:15,420 --> 01:19:19,070
{\an8}So you followed me from
the beach on purpose?</font>

880
01:19:19,080 --> 01:19:23,430
{\an8}Oh no. I've been following
you much further than that!</font>

881
01:19:28,840 --> 01:19:30,150
{\an8}Dr. Golan?!</font>

882
01:19:30,160 --> 01:19:35,360
{\an8}Sometimes when it suits me...
the breadth of</font>

883
01:19:35,360 --> 01:19:41,120
{\an8}my peculiarity is purely
limited by my imagination ..</font>

884
01:19:41,130 --> 01:19:43,570
{\an8}The only thing I can't change...</font>

885
01:19:45,890 --> 01:19:48,380
{\an8}is my eyes.</font>

886
01:19:54,430 --> 01:19:56,960
{\an8}Mr. Barron, How do you do?</font>

887
01:19:58,670 --> 01:20:05,040
{\an8}I saw you, at your grandfather's.
I was hoping to get.</font>

888
01:20:05,110 --> 01:20:08,990
{\an8}Ms. Peregrine's address
from him, but alas...</font>

889
01:20:09,000 --> 01:20:13,120
{\an8}my traveling companion got
to him before I did...</font>

890
01:20:14,730 --> 01:20:18,950
{\an8}and as you know, there's no
stopping a hungry Hollowgasts.</font>

891
01:20:18,960 --> 01:20:24,640
{\an8}Speaking of my traveling companion...
he's coming.</font>

892
01:20:25,650 --> 01:20:27,980
{\an8}And believe me when I say to you</font>

893
01:20:27,990 --> 01:20:33,070
{\an8}you don't want to be here.
When he arrives.</font>

894
01:20:33,080 --> 01:20:40,170
{\an8}So, lets be on your way...
shall we?</font>

895
01:20:57,210 --> 01:20:58,470
{\an8}I mustn't forget our calendar.</font>

896
01:20:58,480 --> 01:21:00,890
{\an8}Could you fetch it from the
parlor please, Miss Avocet?</font>

897
01:21:04,880 --> 01:21:06,390
{\an8}Go and help the others.</font>

898
01:21:19,810 --> 01:21:25,020
{\an8}Miss. Peregrinee what a
pleasure to meet you, at last!</font>

899
01:21:25,030 --> 01:21:26,540
{\an8}May we come in?</font>

900
01:21:33,280 --> 01:21:37,370
{\an8}Children, would you make your
way down the stairs please?</font>

901
01:21:37,380 --> 01:21:40,480
{\an8}I give the orders in
this house, Mr. Baron!</font>

902
01:21:40,480 --> 01:21:41,740
{\an8}Not today.</font>

903
01:21:41,760 --> 01:21:45,260
{\an8}You should know that Jake
has served his purpose.</font>

904
01:21:45,270 --> 01:21:46,800
{\an8}If you value his life</font>

905
01:21:46,800 --> 01:21:51,000
{\an8}I suggest everyone does as
they are told! Children!</font>

906
01:21:53,040 --> 01:21:56,970
{\an8}Shush! No one tells my
children what to do.</font>

907
01:21:56,980 --> 01:21:59,930
{\an8}Children come down here, please.</font>

908
01:22:04,030 --> 01:22:06,800
{\an8}Ms. Peregrine...
I thought I told you to be quiet!</font>

909
01:22:09,780 --> 01:22:15,720
{\an8}Children, for jake's safety, we are
going to do what Mr. Barron asks.</font>

910
01:22:15,720 --> 01:22:18,620
{\an8}He wishes to take me with him
to his rendezvous in Blackpool.</font>

911
01:22:18,630 --> 01:22:22,230
{\an8}So for his protection, he would
like me to assume bird-form,</font>

912
01:22:22,240 --> 01:22:24,190
{\an8}preferably caged...</font>

913
01:22:24,270 --> 01:22:27,750
{\an8}And he'd like you to make your way into
a lockable room, such as the parlor.</font>

914
01:22:27,760 --> 01:22:28,800
{\an8}As he wont release Jake</font>

915
01:22:28,810 --> 01:22:32,290
{\an8}if he fears an attack could be mounted
upon him once he loses his leverage.</font>

916
01:22:33,540 --> 01:22:35,330
{\an8}Correct, Mr. Barron?</font>

917
01:22:35,340 --> 01:22:40,430
{\an8}You are sacrificing yourself
and all of us... for Jake?</font>

918
01:22:40,430 --> 01:22:43,810
{\an8}Mr. Barron travels
with a Hollow, Enoch.</font>

919
01:22:43,820 --> 01:22:46,950
{\an8}Once it arrives here,
we're all dead.</font>

920
01:22:48,080 --> 01:22:50,610
{\an8}Enoch, only Jake can see them.</font>

921
01:22:50,620 --> 01:22:53,230
{\an8}She means he's our only hope.</font>

922
01:23:37,530 --> 01:23:42,900
{\an8}It's been my privilege,
to care for you all.</font>

923
01:23:42,920 --> 01:23:45,540
{\an8}Goodbye! My children.</font>

924
01:23:55,900 --> 01:23:57,600
{\an8}Now, let him go.</font>

925
01:24:19,870 --> 01:24:23,730
{\an8}Promise me one thing, Jake.</font>

926
01:24:23,740 --> 01:24:29,970
{\an8}That you will try to
look after them all.</font>

927
01:24:29,980 --> 01:24:31,900
{\an8}I Promise.</font>

928
01:25:09,260 --> 01:25:12,210
{\an8}Its getting dark. You won't even
be able to see their shadows.</font>

929
01:25:12,220 --> 01:25:15,110
{\an8}We have to stay inside. Its the
only place we stand a chance.</font>

930
01:25:15,110 --> 01:25:16,480
{\an8}He's quite right.</font>

931
01:25:16,490 --> 01:25:20,460
{\an8}Now where does Miss.
Peregrine keep her weapon?</font>

932
01:25:20,820 --> 01:25:22,380
{\an8}Now... all right children.</font>

933
01:25:22,400 --> 01:25:25,340
{\an8}Make sure all the doors are locked
and the windows are latched.</font>

934
01:25:25,350 --> 01:25:28,320
{\an8}Everything must be sealed up tight.
Now quickly, quickly go.</font>

935
01:25:44,130 --> 01:25:47,960
{\an8}Jake, I think tonight
you better answer that.</font>

936
01:25:53,010 --> 01:25:56,920
{\an8}Hello?</font>

937
01:25:59,550 --> 01:26:02,640
{\an8}You... you don't know me.
I'm Jake.</font>

938
01:26:02,650 --> 01:26:07,100
{\an8}Ah! You're new. Well,
welcome to the family Jake.</font>

939
01:26:07,100 --> 01:26:08,480
{\an8}Now I can't talk long,</font>

940
01:26:08,490 --> 01:26:12,680
{\an8}so just tell Miss Peregrine that
I'm at the airbase, and I'm fine.</font>

941
01:26:15,150 --> 01:26:18,730
{\an8}I just wanted to say
that, I miss you</font>

942
01:26:18,740 --> 01:26:22,600
{\an8}and if I disappointed
you, I'm sorry...</font>

943
01:26:22,610 --> 01:26:26,470
{\an8}and you're the best
grandpa in the world.</font>

944
01:26:51,750 --> 01:26:53,220
{\an8}- Fiona!
- Got it!</font>

945
01:26:54,220 --> 01:26:59,590
{\an8}Miss. Avocet! Now children, now that
you are all here, there's a few rules.</font>

946
01:26:59,600 --> 01:27:03,470
{\an8}Your primary job is to stay safe.
Leave the Hollow to me.</font>

947
01:27:03,480 --> 01:27:05,680
{\an8}I don't want to see any heroics.</font>

948
01:27:05,680 --> 01:27:10,550
{\an8}Now, those of you with garden tools,
I must insist that you...</font>

949
01:27:33,830 --> 01:27:35,360
{\an8}No Enoch! Get back!</font>

950
01:28:01,510 --> 01:28:03,440
{\an8}Go! Get to the attic.</font>

951
01:28:06,560 --> 01:28:07,620
{\an8}Take her!</font>

952
01:28:21,950 --> 01:28:25,450
{\an8}Go! Go! Get out! All Come on.</font>

953
01:28:42,490 --> 01:28:46,260
{\an8}Alright... crap! Its almost reset.</font>

954
01:28:50,500 --> 01:28:53,700
{\an8}Fiona, is there anything you can do
with that tree?</font>

955
01:28:53,800 --> 01:28:54,840
{\an8}Be careful!</font>

956
01:28:58,450 --> 01:29:00,750
{\an8}We're going through the windows.
Lets go!</font>

957
01:29:25,390 --> 01:29:26,460
{\an8}Come on!</font>

958
01:29:36,850 --> 01:29:38,220
{\an8}Claire! Come on down.</font>

959
01:30:12,150 --> 01:30:13,520
{\an8}Go Fiona!</font>

960
01:30:21,300 --> 01:30:22,370
{\an8}Let's move on!</font>

961
01:30:46,210 --> 01:30:50,880
{\an8}- What was that?
- The loop closing. It is gone.</font>

962
01:31:12,060 --> 01:31:15,380
{\an8}I'm sorry Jake?
What do we do now?</font>

963
01:31:15,400 --> 01:31:18,330
{\an8}Is there any sign of Barron...</font>

964
01:31:18,330 --> 01:31:23,710
{\an8}- and Miss. Peregrinee?
- Gone. Barron must have had a boat.</font>

965
01:31:27,420 --> 01:31:31,120
{\an8}Well, we have to go after them.
We know he is taking her to Blackpool.</font>

966
01:31:31,130 --> 01:31:33,560
{\an8}But Blackpool is miles
away, and the next ferry</font>

967
01:31:33,560 --> 01:31:37,040
{\an8}doesn't go for hours..
We'll never make it in time.</font>

968
01:31:37,040 --> 01:31:39,900
{\an8}Not unless we go by boat too!</font>

969
01:33:25,800 --> 01:33:30,140
{\an8}So there's a loop here in Blackpool,
its only six months old.</font>

970
01:33:30,150 --> 01:33:33,240
{\an8}January 11th, 2016.
With Miss. Avocet gone...</font>

971
01:33:33,240 --> 01:33:37,110
{\an8}- It can't be reset.
- Won't the loop closes?</font>

972
01:33:37,120 --> 01:33:39,900
{\an8}Then its back to real time.</font>

973
01:33:40,530 --> 01:33:43,600
{\an8}Jake, you know what
this means, don't you?</font>

974
01:33:43,610 --> 01:33:45,100
{\an8}You're going to die.</font>

975
01:33:45,100 --> 01:33:46,790
{\an8}Thats not what I mean.</font>

976
01:33:46,800 --> 01:33:50,460
{\an8}We have to get to our own time.
But you don't.</font>

977
01:33:50,480 --> 01:33:53,120
{\an8}You can continue
to live in 2016.</font>

978
01:33:53,950 --> 01:33:55,490
{\an8}But why would I do that?</font>

979
01:33:55,500 --> 01:33:59,850
{\an8}If we kill Barron,
he'll be gone but time will carry on.</font>

980
01:33:59,860 --> 01:34:02,360
{\an8}He won't go to Florida,</font>

981
01:34:02,370 --> 01:34:06,270
{\an8}Abe won't die and
you can go home.</font>

982
01:34:09,140 --> 01:34:10,880
{\an8}I can see my grandpa.</font>

983
01:34:15,990 --> 01:34:17,950
{\an8}Listen! I can explain
everything to them.</font>

984
01:34:17,960 --> 01:34:20,100
{\an8}I can persuade them to
take me to the island.</font>

985
01:34:21,700 --> 01:34:27,510
{\an8}Will you still there?
Our old loop's gone... for good.</font>

986
01:34:28,580 --> 01:34:31,350
{\an8}We wouldn't see
each other again.</font>

987
01:34:31,360 --> 01:34:33,960
{\an8}I thought you wanted me to stay</font>

988
01:34:37,260 --> 01:34:42,800
{\an8}I know you'll choose Abe.
If I minded I wouldn't have told you.</font>

989
01:34:51,790 --> 01:34:55,330
{\an8}So, we found Miss. Avocet's
loop on the map yet?</font>

990
01:34:55,340 --> 01:34:59,230
{\an8}Its here, but its new, she
made it earlier this year.</font>

991
01:34:59,230 --> 01:35:00,150
{\an8}Its my year.</font>

992
01:35:00,170 --> 01:35:03,840
{\an8}If we don't get out before it closes,
we're stuck in January 2016.</font>

993
01:35:03,850 --> 01:35:08,320
{\an8}Great! So time catches up with all of us,
we all die except you!</font>

994
01:35:08,320 --> 01:35:09,970
{\an8}Plan? Loop closes at 4:30.</font>

995
01:35:09,980 --> 01:35:14,020
{\an8}I mean, we need to get in, rescue
the Ymbrynes... and get out.</font>

996
01:35:14,020 --> 01:35:15,390
{\an8}If we're not dead already.</font>

997
01:35:15,400 --> 01:35:19,600
{\an8}Miss. Avocet said the machine is in the
cellar of the Blackpool tower building.</font>

998
01:35:19,610 --> 01:35:22,280
{\an8}That means we'll be
indoors with Hollows.</font>

999
01:35:22,290 --> 01:35:26,420
{\an8}No... we wont! I've got a plan,
but I'm going to need your help.</font>

1000
01:35:57,270 --> 01:36:01,340
{\an8}- This can't be it, can it?
- Loop entrances can be anywhere.</font>

1001
01:36:01,340 --> 01:36:03,750
{\an8}The one in london is in a subway tunnel.</font>

1002
01:36:16,580 --> 01:36:21,880
{\an8}- Sure, this is it?
- I think so</font>

1003
01:36:23,950 --> 01:36:27,540
{\an8}Miller, there's something
I need you to do first.</font>

1004
01:36:27,560 --> 01:36:28,780
{\an8}Alright, I know.</font>

1005
01:36:31,940 --> 01:36:35,360
{\an8}Look! There's the tower.
Its not far.</font>

1006
01:36:35,370 --> 01:36:38,250
{\an8}Easy for you say! I'm freezing.</font>

1007
01:36:43,760 --> 01:36:45,130
{\an8}Ready?</font>

1008
01:36:56,220 --> 01:37:00,950
{\an8}All the doors to the cellar are locked.
The only way to reach the Ymbrines is...</font>

1009
01:37:00,950 --> 01:37:04,590
{\an8}- Thats backstage.
- How many Hollows can you see?</font>

1010
01:37:05,190 --> 01:37:07,820
{\an8}Four. Its good news.</font>

1011
01:37:07,830 --> 01:37:10,530
{\an8}I think you and I have a very
different definition of good news.</font>

1012
01:37:10,740 --> 01:37:13,610
{\an8}It means Barron's other friends
haven't arrived yet...</font>

1013
01:37:13,610 --> 01:37:19,190
{\an8}Means they haven't started the experiment.
We're not too late.</font>

1014
01:37:20,390 --> 01:37:24,010
{\an8}Okay Emma, you ready?
You know what to say.</font>

1015
01:37:24,020 --> 01:37:25,020
{\an8}Hey, Jake.</font>

1016
01:37:27,730 --> 01:37:31,070
{\an8}Our brethren should be
joining us momentarily.</font>

1017
01:37:31,080 --> 01:37:32,280
{\an8}This is a day...</font>

1018
01:37:32,280 --> 01:37:33,750
{\an8}Hey! You down there.</font>

1019
01:37:33,760 --> 01:37:36,670
{\an8}We killed your Hollow
friend Mr. Barron</font>

1020
01:37:36,680 --> 01:37:39,650
{\an8}and now we've come for
Miss. Peregrinee.</font>

1021
01:37:39,660 --> 01:37:42,940
{\an8}Bring her and all the other
Ymbrines to the end of the pier</font>

1022
01:37:42,950 --> 01:37:46,170
{\an8}in five minutes... or
face the consequences.</font>

1023
01:37:49,840 --> 01:37:53,530
{\an8}These children must be as
insane as their headmistress</font>

1024
01:37:53,540 --> 01:37:57,840
{\an8}Still... the Hollows
will be glad of a feed.</font>

1025
01:38:00,860 --> 01:38:02,460
{\an8}Where are you?</font>

1026
01:38:02,470 --> 01:38:05,980
{\an8}I know you're in here somewhere.</font>

1027
01:38:06,590 --> 01:38:10,660
{\an8}Ah... good..., listen to me.</font>

1028
01:38:10,670 --> 01:38:13,390
{\an8}I want you to follow
Mr. Archer...</font>

1029
01:38:13,420 --> 01:38:14,720
{\an8}and Mr. Clark.</font>

1030
01:38:14,730 --> 01:38:19,940
{\an8}They are going to take you down to
the pier for a little afternoon tea.</font>

1031
01:38:21,170 --> 01:38:22,600
{\an8}Mr. Archer, Mr. Clark,</font>

1032
01:38:22,610 --> 01:38:25,680
{\an8}gather the Hollows and
take them to the pier.</font>

1033
01:38:25,770 --> 01:38:27,060
{\an8}Those children killed Malphus?</font>

1034
01:38:27,070 --> 01:38:29,640
{\an8}Barron has had it for Malphus
since he killed Abe Portman.</font>

1035
01:38:29,650 --> 01:38:34,430
{\an8}Thats Abe Portman for months.</font>

1036
01:38:35,490 --> 01:38:37,160
{\an8}All I needed was a few minutes</font>

1037
01:38:37,170 --> 01:38:40,330
{\an8}to get the location of Miss.
Peregrine's loop from him.</font>

1038
01:38:40,330 --> 01:38:41,900
{\an8}But no.</font>

1039
01:38:41,910 --> 01:38:45,570
{\an8}Malphus couldn't
wait and instead</font>

1040
01:38:45,580 --> 01:38:48,150
{\an8}I had to masquerade as</font>

1041
01:38:48,150 --> 01:38:56,150
{\an8}a psychiatrist for three weeks in Florida.
Have you ever been to Florida?</font>

1042
01:39:01,670 --> 01:39:04,030
{\an8}Did I not tell you to
gather the Hollows?</font>

1043
01:39:04,040 --> 01:39:05,210
{\an8}What if it's a trap?</font>

1044
01:39:05,210 --> 01:39:08,100
{\an8}Of course it is Miss. Edwards!
But what of it?</font>

1045
01:39:08,120 --> 01:39:12,300
{\an8}A couple of children against four Hollows.
Lets get this over with.</font>

1046
01:39:31,560 --> 01:39:33,030
{\an8}Jake, I'm atuck!</font>

1047
01:39:39,370 --> 01:39:40,580
{\an8}Hurry up!</font>

1048
01:40:02,150 --> 01:40:03,350
{\an8}They are coming!</font>

1049
01:40:27,330 --> 01:40:29,160
{\an8}Enoch now!</font>

1050
01:40:47,940 --> 01:40:49,200
{\an8}Go now!</font>

1051
01:41:02,190 --> 01:41:03,830
{\an8}Can be seen now.</font>

1052
01:41:12,280 --> 01:41:13,350
{\an8}Emma! Go!</font>

1053
01:41:17,020 --> 01:41:19,150
{\an8}Don't just stand there!
Get them!</font>

1054
01:43:05,580 --> 01:43:08,340
{\an8}Alright, good job guys.
Time for Step 2.</font>

1055
01:43:08,350 --> 01:43:09,890
{\an8}Save the Ms. Peregrine.</font>

1056
01:43:09,890 --> 01:43:15,270
{\an8}That's... sort of step 3.
First we've got to deal with Barron.</font>

1057
01:43:17,770 --> 01:43:21,440
{\an8}- They should've been back by now.
- I said it was a trap.</font>

1058
01:43:21,440 --> 01:43:26,420
{\an8}If thats true, perhaps we
should move the Ymbrynes now.</font>

1059
01:43:27,230 --> 01:43:28,700
{\an8}You are not serious?</font>

1060
01:43:28,710 --> 01:43:32,960
{\an8}Do I not look serious? Do I
not look like a man who has</font>

1061
01:43:32,960 --> 01:43:38,670
{\an8}trudged the globe looking for just one
more eye to eat in hopes of regaining ..</font>

1062
01:43:38,680 --> 01:43:42,180
{\an8}sufficient humanity to
return to his research?</font>

1063
01:43:42,190 --> 01:43:44,050
{\an8}A man who spent years...</font>

1064
01:43:44,050 --> 01:43:48,290
{\an8}hunting Ymbrynes in
preparation for this night?</font>

1065
01:43:48,300 --> 01:43:51,030
{\an8}And 2...no..3 days in Wales ..</font>

1066
01:43:51,040 --> 01:43:58,880
{\an8}Pretending to look at birds.
I assure you I'll will not stand idly by.</font>

1067
01:43:58,880 --> 01:44:02,580
{\an8}To see my destiny derailed.</font>

1068
01:44:09,060 --> 01:44:10,430
{\an8}Hugh, do it now!</font>

1069
01:44:24,760 --> 01:44:27,260
{\an8}Come back here! Get them!</font>

1070
01:44:35,210 --> 01:44:37,150
{\an8}Low, get down!</font>

1071
01:44:37,160 --> 01:44:42,130
{\an8}You think you can
stand in my way?</font>

1072
01:44:42,130 --> 01:44:43,730
{\an8}You Jake,</font>

1073
01:44:43,740 --> 01:44:50,140
{\an8}content to age and die as if you had
not the gift of peculiarity, at all?</font>

1074
01:44:55,450 --> 01:45:02,420
{\an8}I am a higher being.
I hold a secret to eternal life.</font>

1075
01:45:02,420 --> 01:45:05,340
{\an8}- Sorry to interrupt.
- What the...?</font>

1076
01:45:15,980 --> 01:45:17,490
{\an8}Bronwyn.</font>

1077
01:45:23,830 --> 01:45:25,570
{\an8}You missed me again, Jake.</font>

1078
01:45:25,580 --> 01:45:28,510
{\an8}I take it, accuracy is
not you peculiarity.</font>

1079
01:45:40,130 --> 01:45:42,770
{\an8}Abe was a much worthier adversary.</font>

1080
01:45:45,870 --> 01:45:47,880
{\an8}Don't let him get to the birds!</font>

1081
01:45:59,330 --> 01:46:02,730
{\an8}You must put me in contact
with your tailor.</font>

1082
01:46:04,540 --> 01:46:08,720
{\an8}Ymbrynes...
Ymbrynes, here I come!</font>

1083
01:46:20,640 --> 01:46:23,840
{\an8}Cold. Wait till the blood
freezes in your veins.</font>

1084
01:46:28,780 --> 01:46:31,430
{\an8}That was your attempt to
rescue your friend? Was it?</font>

1085
01:46:56,070 --> 01:46:58,270
{\an8}Jake!
I'll hold him as long as I can</font>

1086
01:46:58,270 --> 01:47:01,920
{\an8}when are you going to realise you are
a terrible shot with that thing?</font>

1087
01:47:01,940 --> 01:47:03,880
{\an8}Get the others,
I'll meet you at the.</font>

1088
01:47:03,880 --> 01:47:05,380
{\an8}Loop entrance.</font>

1089
01:47:19,000 --> 01:47:20,210
{\an8}He's getting out.</font>

1090
01:47:48,960 --> 01:47:52,520
{\an8}Eventually you're going
to run out of breath</font>

1091
01:47:52,530 --> 01:47:56,270
{\an8}and it'll all be over.</font>

1092
01:47:56,280 --> 01:48:00,000
{\an8}Death for your beloved Jake
and Miss Megan Peregrinee...</font>

1093
01:48:00,010 --> 01:48:04,390
{\an8}and everlasting life for me.</font>

1094
01:49:02,560 --> 01:49:04,630
{\an8}Olive! Olive!</font>

1095
01:49:08,800 --> 01:49:10,560
{\an8}I'm so sorry, Olive.</font>

1096
01:49:10,570 --> 01:49:14,180
{\an8}All these years I never
appreciated you.</font>

1097
01:49:14,190 --> 01:49:17,520
{\an8}I didn't see how lucky I was.</font>

1098
01:49:19,660 --> 01:49:23,640
{\an8}I got so used to having you
there, I never realized.</font>

1099
01:49:31,280 --> 01:49:33,050
{\an8}You never realised, what?</font>

1100
01:50:22,470 --> 01:50:24,850
{\an8}Find your children.
Create new loops.</font>

1101
01:50:28,090 --> 01:50:29,580
{\an8}So Jake,</font>

1102
01:50:29,590 --> 01:50:33,230
{\an8}I see you've inherited your
grandfather's peculiarity.</font>

1103
01:50:33,240 --> 01:50:35,550
{\an8}You're just as
annoying as he was.</font>

1104
01:50:38,670 --> 01:50:43,720
{\an8}Speaking of Abe, if you should
see him in the afterlife,</font>

1105
01:50:43,730 --> 01:50:45,590
{\an8}Give him my regards.</font>

1106
01:50:53,770 --> 01:50:56,470
{\an8}Please, we can't risk
him taking you again.</font>

1107
01:51:15,540 --> 01:51:16,700
{\an8}Enoch! Where are the others?</font>

1108
01:51:16,710 --> 01:51:19,010
{\an8}There safe. Olive is leading
them back to the ghost ship.</font>

1109
01:51:19,010 --> 01:51:21,150
{\an8}Jake needs us.
Barron's too strong.</font>

1110
01:51:28,700 --> 01:51:31,900
{\an8}You've lost Miss. Peregrine.
You've lost everything!</font>

1111
01:51:31,910 --> 01:51:33,010
{\an8}Its over!</font>

1112
01:51:46,260 --> 01:51:47,930
{\an8}Jake?</font>

1113
01:51:51,540 --> 01:51:53,510
{\an8}Jake?</font>

1114
01:51:56,780 --> 01:51:58,480
{\an8}Jake?</font>

1115
01:52:04,760 --> 01:52:07,870
{\an8}Emma? Wait, thats not me.
It is Barron.</font>

1116
01:52:07,870 --> 01:52:10,900
{\an8}Don't listen to him. He is Barron.
I'm Jake. That's Barron.</font>

1117
01:52:12,200 --> 01:52:15,650
{\an8}Well I got better shot than Jake.
So neither of you move till we sort this.</font>

1118
01:52:15,650 --> 01:52:16,930
{\an8}Listen to me. I'm Jake.</font>

1119
01:52:16,940 --> 01:52:19,950
{\an8}I grew up in Florida and I
wanted to be an explorer.</font>

1120
01:52:19,950 --> 01:52:22,790
{\an8}I never thought nothing would ever
change because I was ordinary.</font>

1121
01:52:22,790 --> 01:52:24,160
{\an8}Thats Jake get Barron.</font>

1122
01:52:24,170 --> 01:52:27,460
{\an8}Wait! I told him all this.
She was my psychiatrist.</font>

1123
01:52:27,470 --> 01:52:30,140
{\an8}You deal with him.
I'll go find Miss. Peregrinee.</font>

1124
01:52:38,180 --> 01:52:44,870
{\an8}Wait. I can prove that I'm me,
because I am not ordinary</font>

1125
01:52:47,770 --> 01:52:49,740
{\an8}I can do something
that no one else can</font>

1126
01:52:58,160 --> 01:53:00,390
{\an8}I can see the monsters.</font>

1127
01:53:08,940 --> 01:53:11,950
{\an8}Wait, it's me!</font>

1128
01:53:27,780 --> 01:53:28,780
{\an8}Enoch!</font>

1129
01:53:44,910 --> 01:53:47,790
{\an8}We need to go.
The loop is closing.</font>

1130
01:53:47,800 --> 01:53:48,920
{\an8}Yeah.</font>

1131
01:53:50,010 --> 01:53:51,750
{\an8}Those of us who are leaving.</font>

1132
01:54:57,280 --> 01:54:58,340
{\an8}Emma...</font>

1133
01:54:58,360 --> 01:55:01,610
{\an8}You love your grandfather.
There's nothing more to explain.</font>

1134
01:55:01,610 --> 01:55:04,790
{\an8}No, I promised Miss Peregrine
that I'd look after you all</font>

1135
01:55:04,800 --> 01:55:08,020
{\an8}and with her injured and
you without a loop...</font>

1136
01:55:08,030 --> 01:55:12,900
{\an8}She'll recover and until
then we'll be in 1943.</font>

1137
01:55:12,920 --> 01:55:18,240
{\an8}We'll only age one day at a time.
Like normal people,</font>

1138
01:55:18,250 --> 01:55:22,250
{\an8}- Which can be no bad thing.
- And what about the Hollows?</font>

1139
01:55:22,250 --> 01:55:26,390
{\an8}As long as they are out
there, you are not safe.</font>

1140
01:55:26,390 --> 01:55:29,340
{\an8}We don't need you to
make us feel safe, Jake.</font>

1141
01:55:29,350 --> 01:55:33,780
{\an8}Because you made us feel brave.
And thats even better.</font>

1142
01:56:36,420 --> 01:56:38,390
{\an8}Cmon guys, lets go!</font>

1143
01:57:21,970 --> 01:57:29,970
{\an8}And then we said goodbye and loop closed.
I was so scared that you wouldn't be here.</font>

1144
01:57:32,920 --> 01:57:37,030
{\an8}I'd never see you again.
I am safe.</font>

1145
01:57:40,640 --> 01:57:47,750
{\an8}Let me give you your birthday present.
Grandpa, my birthday isn't for months.</font>

1146
01:57:51,420 --> 01:57:55,010
{\an8}For your travels. Go to her.
Jake.</font>

1147
01:57:55,020 --> 01:57:59,430
{\an8}You have the map.
You can go back to 1943.</font>

1148
01:58:05,150 --> 01:58:09,280
{\an8}Even so, they took a boat.
I don't know where they are.</font>

1149
01:58:11,530 --> 01:58:14,260
{\an8}But you know where they were.</font>

1150
01:58:52,800 --> 01:58:56,500
{\an8}You have no idea how long
it took me to get here.</font>

1151
01:58:59,050 --> 01:59:01,720
{\an8}The closest loop was in
the California desert.</font>

1152
01:59:09,860 --> 01:59:12,510
{\an8}I used it to get
to the Tokyo loop.</font>

1153
01:59:16,610 --> 01:59:19,900
{\an8}That led me to the nearest
loop back in 1942,</font>

1154
01:59:19,910 --> 01:59:23,190
{\an8}where I wound up joining the navy.
Don't ask.</font>

1155
01:59:24,000 --> 01:59:26,500
{\an8}Then I spent 2 months
in London trying...</font>

1156
01:59:53,240 --> 01:59:55,950
{\an8}Ready. Full speed ahead!</font>

